## GitOps Controller

This repository uses **{{if eq (printf "%s" .Controller.Type) "argocd"}}ArgoCD{{else}}Flux CD{{end}}** (v{{.Controller.Version}}) as the GitOps controller.

{{- if eq (printf "%s" .Controller.Type) "argocd"}}
## App of Apps Pattern

The `apps/` directory follows the [App of Apps pattern](https://argo-cd.readthedocs.io/en/stable/operator-manual/cluster-bootstrapping/#app-of-apps-pattern):

- `apps/_root.yaml` is the **root Application** that watches the `apps/` directory.
- Each file in `apps/` defines an ArgoCD Application pointing to an environment overlay.
- Adding a new Application YAML to `apps/` automatically onboards it — no manual ArgoCD configuration needed.
{{- else}}
## Flux Reconciliation Model

The `apps/` directory contains Flux Kustomization CRDs that drive reconciliation:

- `apps/_root.yaml` defines a **GitRepository** source and a root **Kustomization** that watches `apps/`.
- Each file in `apps/` is a Flux `Kustomization` pointing to an environment overlay.
- Adding a new Kustomization YAML to `apps/` automatically onboards it — Flux picks up changes on the configured interval.
{{- end}}

## Kustomize Base + Overlays

Application manifests use [Kustomize](https://kustomize.io/) with a base + overlay structure:

- **`environments/base/<app>/`** contains the canonical manifests (Deployment, Service, etc.).
- **`environments/<env>/<app>/`** contains an overlay that patches the base for that environment (replica count, namespace, labels).

This makes environment differences **explicit and auditable** in version control.

